attributes.title: Odd Harmonious Labelings Of Cyclic Snakes
attributes.description: In [8] Liang and Bai have shown that the kC4 − snake graph is an odd harmonious graph for each k ≥ 1. In this paper we generalize this result on cycles by showing that the kCn − snake with string 1,1,…,1 when n ≡ 0 (mod 4) are odd harmonious graph. Also we show that the kC4 − snake with m-pendant edges for each k,m ≥ 1 , (for linear case and for general case). Moreover, we show that, all subdivision of 2 m∆k - snake are odd harmonious for each k,m ≥ 1 . Finally we present some examples to illustrate the proposed theories

attributes.title: Figure 1 In Aipysurus Mosaicus, A New Species Of Egg-Eating Sea Snake (Elapidae: Hydrophiinae), With A Redescription Of Aipysurus Eydouxii (Gray, 1849)
attributes.description: FIGURE 1. MrBayes all compatible consensus of 4000 post burn-in trees for the Aipysurus and Emydocephalus specimens sampled in this study based on the concatenated mitochondrial data (Hydrophis caerulescens outgroup not shown). Scale bar indicates the number of nucleotide substitutions per site. Node support values (posterior probabilities) above 0.95 are shown.

attributes.title: Figure 2 In Aipysurus Mosaicus, A New Species Of Egg-Eating Sea Snake (Elapidae: Hydrophiinae), With A Redescription Of Aipysurus Eydouxii (Gray, 1849)
attributes.description: FIGURE 2. The single most parsimonious tree for phased haplotypes of the nuclear G 1894 fragment. Scale bar indicates branch lengths corresponding to 1 step.

attributes.title: Figure 3 In Aipysurus Mosaicus, A New Species Of Egg-Eating Sea Snake (Elapidae: Hydrophiinae), With A Redescription Of Aipysurus Eydouxii (Gray, 1849)
attributes.description: FIGURE 3. The single most parsimonious tree for phased haplotypes of the nuclear G 1888 fragment. Scale bar indicates branch lengths corresponding to 1 step.

attributes.title: Figure 4 In Aipysurus Mosaicus, A New Species Of Egg-Eating Sea Snake (Elapidae: Hydrophiinae), With A Redescription Of Aipysurus Eydouxii (Gray, 1849)
attributes.description: FIGURE 4. Full body photographs of A) the holotype of Aipysurus mosaicus sp. nov. from northern Australia (SAMA R 65222) and B) A. eydouxii from Singapore (SAMA R 22569). Grid scale represents 1 x 1 cm. Note that A. mosaicus has fewer bands on the body and tail and that these are less distinct.

attributes.title: Figure 5 In Aipysurus Mosaicus, A New Species Of Egg-Eating Sea Snake (Elapidae: Hydrophiinae), With A Redescription Of Aipysurus Eydouxii (Gray, 1849)
attributes.description: FIGURE 5. Micro-CT images of Aipysurus mosaicus sp. nov. from (A) left lateral and (B) dorsal view of skull, and (C) left lateral view of mid-caudal vertebrae; and Aipysurus eydouxii from (D) left lateral and (E) dorsal view of skull, and (F) left lateral view of mid-caudal vertebrae. Note the differences in the morphology of the premaxilla, maxilla, nasal, frontoparietal suture, and neural spine; see text for fuller discussion. Specimens illustrated are as follows: (A, B) SAMA R 65222 holotype, (C) SAMA R 23493 paratype, (D, E) MZB Ophi 4184, (F) SAMA R 22569.

attributes.description: FIGURE 6. A) Right lateral, B) dorsal, and C) ventral photographs of the head of the holotype of Aipysurus mosaicus sp. nov. (SAMA R 65222). Grid scale represents 1 x 1 cm.
